<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="781" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/639.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Messrs. <gloss type="to">Kuhn, Loeb and Company</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 20, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to Department’s January 6 and your reply same date. It is hoped
                            that fiscal agents and attorneys have reached agreement about payment
                            Liberian interest, and that Department may soon be able to reply to
                            telegram received from American Minister Monrovia.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>